title: George Frideric handel - Complete Wind Sonatas (Flute, oboe, rec
description:
These are all MP3's @ a 256 bit rate.  Sorry they're not in FLAC, I purchased these from an mp3 online store.  

The album artwork is inside of the metadata, so when you transfer it into iTunes or something, the album artwork will appear.  

More info about this album: <a href=" http://www.amazon.com/Handel-Complete-Wind-Sonatas/dp/B000VHKIB8/ref=sr_1_2?ie=UTF8&s=dmusic&qid=1234751880&sr=8-2" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://www.amazon.com/Handel-Complete-Wind-Sonatas/dp/B000VHKIB8/ref=sr_1_2?ie=UTF8&s=dmusic&qid=1234751880&sr=8-2</a>

FYI:  The way I arranged the metadata, the tracks are NOT in the same order as they are when I purchased them.  I arranged them so that all the flute sonatas are together and all of everything else is together as a separate cd. I play flute so I did it that way so that I could listen to JUST flute music by itself for my ipod. 

Also, I will only be seeding this today until about 11pm, central time in USA, because I need to get to sleep early. Sorry for the inconvenience.  I will seed again tomorrow about late afternoon, early eveningish.

Enjoy.  

Can somebody, in the comments section, please tell me how to make a cue/log file from cd's using an apple macbook please?  I have Toast 9 and MAX converter.  Thanks.
